pper-alpha">General rules.</span></strong><ol class=3D"decimal"><li><strong=
><span class=3D"decimal">Applicability</span></strong><span class=3D"decima=
l">&nbsp;The provisions of this Rule 8, other than for Section (F) below, a=
pply to you only if you have a Ticket and a confirmed reserved space on one=
 of our flights and there is a flight delay, flight change, flight diversio=
n, or flight cancellation. If you are a standby guest, your rights are gove=
rned by Section (F) of this Rule 8.</span></li><li><strong><span class=3D"d=
ecimal">Notification.</span></strong><span class=3D"decimal">&nbsp;We will =
promptly notify you of any delay, change, diversion, or cancellation of you=
r confirmed reserved space as soon as reasonably possible after it is confi=
rmed. We will also notify you of aircraft changes. </span></li><li><strong>=
<span class=3D"decimal">Schedules are Subject to Change Without Notice.</sp=
an></strong><span class=3D"decimal">&nbsp;Any times shown on Tickets, timet=
ables, published schedules or elsewhere, as well as any aircraft type and s=
imilar details reflected on any Tickets or in any of our flight schedules a=
re not guaranteed and are not a part of this contract. We may (i) substitut=
e alternate carriers or aircraft, (ii) delay or cancel flights, and (iii) a=
lter or omit stopping places or connections shown on the Ticket at any time=
.</span> However, for passengers departing from Korea, actions shall be tak=
en in accordance with the standards for the protection of air transport use=
rs.</li><li><strong><span class=3D"decimal">Liability.</span></strong><span=
 class=3D"decimal">&nbsp;Except to the extent provided in this Rule 8 or ot=
herwise required by Applicable Laws, we are not liable for failing to opera=
te any flight according to schedule, or for any change in flight schedule, =
with or without notice to you.</span></li></ol></li><li><strong>Flight Canc=
ellations and Significantly Delayed or Changed Flights.</strong><span class=
=3D"upper-alpha">The following rules apply to any Cancellation or Significa=
ntly Delayed to Changed Flight:</span><ol class=3D"decimal"><li><strong>Lia=
bility</strong>.<span class=3D"decimal">&nbsp;</span>Except as provided by =
Applicable Laws, we are not liable for any Flight Cancellation or Significa=
ntly Delayed or Changed Flight.</li><li><strong>Flight Cancellations and Si=
gnificantly Delayed or Change Flights. </strong>When your ticket is affecte=
d by any Flight Cancellation or Significantly Delayed or Changed Flight, yo=
u have a nonrefundable ticket and we are the merchant of record, we will ad=
vise you of your right to a refund for any affected segments and refund you=
r ticket in accordance with Rule 17, using the original form of payment, if=
:</li><ol class=3D"lower-alpha"><li><span class=3D"lower-alpha">you decide =
not to fly on the Significantly Delayed or Changed Flight;</span></li><li><=
span class=3D"lower-alpha">do not accept rebooking on an alternative flight=
 we may offer you or we cannot offer you an alternative itinerary, and</spa=
n></li><li><span class=3D"lower-alpha">do not accept a voucher, if offered =
to you.</span><span class=3D"lower-alpha">
<br></span><span class=3D"lower-alpha">Note: If we are unable to transport =
you in the same class of service you originally booked and you decide to tr=
avel in a lower class of service, we will provide a refund of the differenc=
e in fare.</span></li></ol></ol></li><li><p>For Passengers departing from a=
n airport located in the EEA or the UK, who are entitled to make a claim fo=
r compensation for a Significantly delayed or Changed Flight or denied boar=
ding under Applicable Laws, the following applies:</p></li><ol class=3D"dec=
imal"><li><p>A claim must be submitted directly to Alaska, either through A=
laska's website or by writing to Alaska customer relations. The Passenger m=
ust allow Alaska 28 days (or such time as permitted by Applicable Law, whic=
hever is the shorter) to respond, before engaging a third party to bring a =
claim on the Passenger's behalf.</p></li><li><p>Passengers entitled to brin=
g a claim for compensation are not prevented by this clause from consulting=
 a legal adviser or third-party company before submitting a claim to Alaska=
.</p></li><li><p>Alaska will not deal with any claim submitted by a third p=
arty company on behalf of Passengers if the process at Rule 8 C1 has not be=
